definition.value: A tricarboxylic acid trianion resulting from the deprotonation of all three carboxy groups of 3-hydroxybutane-1,2,3-tricarboxylic acid; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A D-valine residue that is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4.
An L-valine residue that is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3.
An L-tryptophan residue that is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3.

A glycopentaosylceramide in which the galactose residue at the non-reducing end of the oligosaccharide moiety in beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer is sulfated at O-3.

A beta-D-Gal3S-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer in which the acyl and alkyl chains are respectively tetracosanoyl and 3-hydroxyoctadec-4-en-1-yl.
An L-proline residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4 (the 3R,4S diastereoisomer).
A 3,4-dihydroxy-L-proline residue which has 3R,4R configuration.
An L-proline residue that is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.
An L-phenylalanine residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3', 4' and 5'.
An L-phenylalanine residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3' and 4'.
A nL-lysine residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 5; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An L-lysinium residue that is substituted by an hydroxy group at position 5; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An L-leucine residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4, 5 and 5'.
An L-leucine residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 5 (the 4S stereoisomer).
A tricyclic diterpenoid that is 15,16-epoxydolabrene in which the pro-S hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A tricyclic diterpenoid that is dolabradiene in which vinyl substituent has undergone oxidation to give the corresponding epoxide.

A carbotricyclic compound and diterpene that is tetradecahydrophenanthrene which is substituted by a methylene group at position 1, methyl groups at positions 4b, 7, and 10a, and a vinyl group at position 7 (the 4aS,4bR,7S,8aR,10aS stereoisomer).
An L-leucine residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 5 (the 4R stereoisomer).
An L-leucine residue that is substituted by an hydroxy group at position 5 (the 4R stereoisomer).
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from 4-hydroxy-L-leucine.
An L-isoleucine residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 5 (the 3R,4R diastereoisomer).
An L-isoleucine residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4 (the 3S,4R diastereoisomer).
An L-asparagine residue that is substituted by an hydroxy group at position.
An L-arginine residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion derived from L-cysteate; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An L-tryptophan residue that is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7.
An L-proline residue that is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4.
An L-proline residue that is substituted by an hydroxy group at position 3.
An L-phenylalanine residue that is substituted by an hydroxy group at position 3.
